<br>
I bounded off to the halfling camps and began slaying the lot of them.  The Hafling city was fully popped and I cleaved my way thru the lot of them....chasing a few down as they ran screaming &quot;AAhhhh its Ichi....run!!&quot;  I then made my way to the other camps and made quick work of them.  Upon returning to the first camp I noticed a human monk with grey hair sitting there.  He had a corpse a few feet from the camp when I had arrived the first time.  I stopped and looked around.  He was obviously not killing the halflings so I began to splatter halfling blood and guts all over the vicinity.  Among the hafling screams came a sharp comment from the human....1 word actually....&quot;F..k.r!&quot;<br>
<br>
I not missing a beat continued the onslaught and commented back with.. &quot;Im sorry, where you killing these halflings?&quot;  He aswered that he wasnt and that I should taking my $#%#$^% stinky #$%# and leave!  An onslaught of foul language which I dont feel is RPing ensued from him.  I told him in role play to watch his mouth or id rip it off and shove it someplace not nice.  After a couple more comments instructed him to shut the face.  I then offered to duel him after some empty threats were made on his part.  He declined and ran off.<br>
<br>
I continued killing and eventually returned to this camp to find him sitting there again.  I killed the halflings and left again without too much comment from him.  I returned a bit later and he was dead...lying by the empty camp.<br>
<br>
I chuckled in spite of myself.  I was going to wait and RP some seriously funny stuff as he looted his corpse....but the RL nice guy behind the screen took over (DAMN HIM....Ichi shakes fist at his RL master) and I logged for the evening.<br>
<br>
Just a little tidbit to share.<br>
<br>
Foul language like that is not RPing.  Find a more literate way to communicate.  It makes for a more reasonable atmosphere.  In all likelihood I would have left if he had....but he was an ass so I didnt.<br>
<br>
Ichi<br>
